      "content": "okay that makes sense for the sociological angle. so to take it a step further for my debate, if i'm arguing this side, how would i address the idea that integration actually threatens social stability? like, what are the \"pros\" of maintaining these boundaries to prevent social friction or loss of group identity? i want to be able to argue that total integration might lead to the erosion of these unique cultural identities or cause societal tension. what would be the most effective way to frame that argument so it sounds like a reasoned perspective on social order?",
